{"id": 6616, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2017", "session": "17N", "subtopic": "5-2-hesss-law", "title": "17N.1.SL.TZ0.14", "topic_id": "5", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>The enthalpy changes for two reactions are given.</p>\n<p>Br<sub>2</sub> (l) + F<sub>2</sub> (g) → 2BrF (g)         <em>ΔH</em> = <em>x</em> kJ<br/>Br<sub>2</sub> (l) + 3F<sub>2</sub> (g) → 2BrF<sub>3</sub> (g)      <em>ΔH</em> = <em>y</em> kJ</p>\n<p>What is the enthalpy change for the following reaction?</p>\n<p>BrF (g) + F<sub>2</sub> (g) → BrF<sub>3</sub> (g)</p>\n<p>A.  <em>x</em> – <em>y</em></p>\n<p>B.  –<em>x</em> + <em>y</em></p>\n<p>C.  <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>(–<em>x</em> + <em>y</em>)</p>\n<p>D.  <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>(<em>x</em> – <em>y</em>)</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>C</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}